cz.cvut.fel.matyapav.afandroid.builders

Class AFComponentBuilder<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • cz.cvut.fel.matyapav.afandroid.builders.AFComponentBuilder<T>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    FormBuilder, ListBuilder, TableBuilder

    public abstract class AFComponentBuilder<T>
extends java.lang.Object
    This class defines common parts of all component builders. Specific component builders must extend this class.
    Since:
    1.0.0.

      • initBuilder

        public T initBuilder(Activity activity,
                     java.lang.String componentKeyName,
                     java.io.InputStream connectionResource,
                     java.lang.String connectionKey)
        Initializes builder for component. This method should be used if getting definition of component from server does not need additional parameters like user credentials.
        Parameters:
        activity - needed to dynamically create UI in runtime.
        componentKeyName - user defined name of component
        connectionResource - input stream with XML file, which defines connections
        connectionKey - used to get specific connection definition from connectionResource file.
        Returns:
        concrete builder

      • initializeConnections

        protected void initializeConnections()
                              throws java.lang.Exception
        Initializes connections for component. Creates and sets connections from specified file to builder. Must be called before creating any part of component and after initialization of builder.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - throwed if not connection was specified, that means initialization of builder was not called.

      • prepareComponent

        protected void prepareComponent(com.tomscz.afrest.rest.dto.AFClassInfo classDef,
                                AFComponent component,
                                int numberOfInnerClasses,
                                boolean parsingInnerClass,
                                java.lang.StringBuilder road)
        Prepares whole component especially its graphical representation which can be inserted in UI.
        Parameters:
        classDef - information about component
        component - which component is being prepared
        numberOfInnerClasses - number of inner classes which actual class definition has
        parsingInnerClass - determines if preparing UI from inner class
        road - passed to field buidlers. If not empty, field belongs to some inner class. This fact must be set into fields id.

      • buildComponent

        protected void buildComponent(AFComponent component)
                       throws java.lang.Exception
        Builds and wraps component UI from class definition and sets it to component.
        Parameters:
        component - component its UI is being built wrapped and set.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - thrown if there is some error during parsing component definition or building component view

      • createComponent

        public abstract AFComponent createComponent()
                                     throws java.lang.Exception
        Builder specific method which creates final version of component which is presented to user. Should be used by user to create component.
        Returns:
        completely created component
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - thrown if there is an error during crating process. User must handle this exception.
